<section style="background-color: #f4f4f4; padding: 40px; text-align: center;">
    <h1 style="color: #007bff; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 2.5em; margin-bottom: 20px;">Safeguarding Property Documents from Tampering and Fraud Using Blockchain Technology</h1>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 20px;">Batch No: 26</h2>
    <h3 style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 20px;">Guide Name: Dr. Y Ramesh</h3>
    <p style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;">
        The sector of buying and selling properties usually takes a long time and is complicated. There's also a risk of mistakes and fraud, which might cause big financial losses and legal problems. By using blockchain technology, this project innovatively addresses the pervasive issue of fraud within property documents.
    </p>
    <p style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;">
        Blockchain technology offers a decentralized and tamper-proof solution to address these challenges by providing a secure and transparent platform for recording and verifying property transactions. Our idea involves digitizing property documents, generating unique hashes using the SHA-256 algorithm, and storing these documents on the Interplanetary File System (IPFS) to ensure decentralized and secure storage.
    </p>
    <p style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;">
        Each document's unique content identifier (CID) from IPFS and its SHA-256 hash are recorded on the Ethereum blockchain, ensuring immutability and transparency. The verification process involves retrieving the document from IPFS, generating a new hash, and comparing it with the blockchain record to confirm authenticity. This approach offers significant benefits, including immutability, decentralization, transparency, and enhanced security.
    </p>
    <p style="font-weight: bold; margin-top: 20px;">Keywords: Blockchain Technology, Ethereum, IPFS, Smart contracts</p>
</section>

